  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f2378110",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Column Explanations\n",
    "\n",
    "Date (index) – Trading day.\\\n",
    "Open – Price when the stock first traded that day.\\\n",
    "High – Highest price during that day.\\\n",
    "Low – Lowest price during that day.\\\n",
    "Close – Price at the end of the trading day (this is our target y).\\\n",
    "Volume – Number of shares traded that day.\\\n",
    "Dividends – Dividend issued per share on that day (if any).\\\n",
    "Stock Splits – Stock split ratio (if a split occurred that day)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "56912443",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Choosing Features (X) to Predict Close \n",
    "Since the goal is to predict Close, we need predictors that make sense: \\\n",
    "Good candidates for Features (X): \\\n",
    "Open → starting price of the day (strongly related to Close). \\\n",
    "High → daily max, often correlated with closing price. \\\n",
    "Low → daily min, also correlated. \\\n",
    "Volume → market activity, might influence price movement. \\\n",
    "Not ideal for prediction in this assignment: \\\n",
    "Dividends (rare events, mostly 0). \\\n",
    "Stock Splits (rare events, mostly 0). "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "776e3b9f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = df[[\"Open\", \"High\", \"Low\", \"Volume\"]]\n",
    "y = df[\"Close\"]"
   ]
  },
